          "websocket.js combines connection lifecycle, protocol dispatch, auth/session, and many domain command families.",
          "uploader.js exports a process entrypoint while most of its execution path is disabled/commented."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Refactor around explicit boundaries: transport client, protocol handlers, and per-domain command modules; then either fully implement or fully remove partial upload workflow to restore single-responsibility design.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
